        <h1>Most Iconic Italian Formula 1 Racing Teams</h1>
        <ol>
            <li>Scuderia Ferrari</li>
            <li>Alfa Romeo Corse</li>
            <li>Maserati</li>
            <li>Minardi F1</li>
        </ol>
    </main>

    <h2>Quick Presentation</h2>
    <h3>Scuderia Ferrari</h3>
    <p>Scuderia Ferrari, founded in 1929, is the most iconic team racing in Formula 1. The team, from 1950, founding
        year of Formula 1 championship, has won 16 constructors championships with 15 drivers championships (most by
        the legendary Michael Schumacher).</p>
    <p>For Italians, Ferrari is not just a racing team; it is a symbol of national pride and passion. The prancing
        horse represents the relentless pursuit of excellence and the romantic allure of speed and innovation. Every
        victory is celebrated with fervor, and every race is a testament to the Italian spirit of determination and
        love for motorsport.</p>
    <figure>
        <img src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/18737972/pexels-photo-18737972/free-photo-of-energia-potenza-veloce-velocita.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=1"
            alt="Ferrari Formula 1 Team" width="400" height="250">
        <figcaption>Credit: Adriaan Greyling - <a
                href="https://www.pexels.com/it-it/foto/energia-potenza-veloce-velocita-18737972/">Pexels.com</a>
        </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h3>Alfa Romeo Corse</h3>
    <p>The team has been founded in 1911 and started to race in Formula 1 in 1950. The team participated in several
        editions from 1950 to 1987. This team has won the first two editions of the championship, in 1950 with two
        iconic drivers, the Italian Nino Farina in 1950 and with the Argentine Juan Manuel Fangio in 1951.</p>
    <p>Alfa Romeo holds a special place in the hearts of Italians as the pioneer of their Formula 1 legacy. The
        early triumphs of Nino Farina and Juan Manuel Fangio are cherished memories, symbolizing the dawn of Italian
        dominance in motorsport. Alfa Romeo's legacy is a romantic tale of innovation, speed, and the undying
        Italian passion for racing.</p>
    <figure>
        <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/Alfa_Romeo_Alfetta_159.jpg" alt="Alfa Romeo Corse"
            width="400" height="250">
        <figcaption>Credit: Wikipedia - <a
                href="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/41/Alfa_Romeo_Alfetta_159.jpg">
                Wikimedia website</a>
        </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h3>Maserati Corse</h3>
    <p>The team has been founded in 1926 and participated in Formula 1 editions from 1950 to 1960. Maserati won two
        championships both with the driver Juan Manuel Fangio.</p>
    <p>Maserati's journey in Formula 1 is a story of elegance and excellence. The victories with Juan Manuel Fangio
        are celebrated as milestones of Italian engineering and racing prowess. For Italians, Maserati embodies the
        romantic spirit of competition, where every race is a blend of passion, precision, and the pursuit of
        perfection.</p>
    <figure>
        <img src="https://farm9.staticflickr.com/8308/7915502722_44a4a3b62f_z.jpg" alt="Maserati Corse" width="400"
            height="250">
        <figcaption>Credit: Bas Bloemsaat - <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/basje/7915502722/">
                Flickr.com</a>
        </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h3>Minardi F1</h3>
    <p>The Minardi Formula 1 team, founded in 1979 by the passionate Gian Carlo Minardi, was more than just a racing
        team for Italians; it was a symbol of hope, determination, and national pride. Competing from 1985 to 2005,
        Minardi participated in 340 Grand Prix races. Though they never claimed a victory or stood on the podium,
        their spirit and perseverance captured the hearts of many.</p>
    <p>For Italians, Minardi represented the underdog, the small team that dared to dream big against the giants of
        the sport. It was a story of resilience, where every race was a testament to their unwavering dedication and
        love for motorsport. The team’s journey was a romantic saga of passion and grit, embodying the essence of
        Italian fervor and the relentless pursuit of excellence.</p>
    <p>Minardi’s legacy lives on in the hearts of fans who admired their courage and the way they brought a touch of
        Italian romance to the high-speed world of Formula 1. It was a reminder that sometimes, the greatest
        victories are not measured by trophies, but by the indomitable spirit and the dreams that drive us forward.
    </p>
